<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Spain-EEC     04-15 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Spain-EEC,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Spain Sets European Parliament Election Date</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Spanish government set June 15 as the
date for European parliamentary elections.
   The elections to the assembly based in Strasbourg, France, of
the European Economic Community will be the second for Spain since
it joined the 12-nation trading bloc in January 1986.
   The first elections held June 10, 1987, coincided with city and
regional polls. Of the 60 seats alloted Spain in the assembly,
Gonzalez's ruling Socialist party won 28, the largest conservative
party, Popular Alliance (now the Popular Party) won 17 and the
centrist Democratic Social Center won seven.
</TEXT>
