<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--EEC-Prostitution     04-15 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--EEC-Prostitution,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>European Parliament Calls For Legal War On Prostitution</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STRASBOURG, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European parliament has called for
stiffer legislation against prostitution, saying it is a crime not
unlike slavery.
   In a resolution Friday, the parliament proposed uniform, tougher
penalties on prostitution throughout the 12-country European
Community.
   The 518-member assembly called for giving women involved in
prostitution more educational and job opportunities. It proposed
special aid to women in poorer areas and countries where most
prostitutes come from, including special programs helping country
women adapt to the strains of urban life.
   The assembly also called for measures against pornography and
communication systems that help promote prostitution such as the
French Minitel, a popular teletext network.
</TEXT>
