<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-15 0457</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0471</SECOND>
<HEAD>Showers Extend Across Florida; Fog Shrouds Lower Mississippi Valley</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms extended across much of Florida today,
while a dense fog advisory was posted in Louisiana.
   An upper air disturbance over the southeast United States
produced showers and some thunderstorms Friday from the eastern
half of the Gulf Coast into the Tennessee Valley, parts of the Ohio
Valley, Virginia and the North Carolina coast.
   A narrow band of showers and thunderstorms were along a cold
front that stretched from the eastern half of the upper Great Lakes
to the Texas Panhandle.
   Clear skies and lower temperatures were behind the front, over
the northern and central Plains.
   Fog covered much of the lower Mississippi Valley and the western
half of the Gulf Coast. Some of the fog was dense with visibilities
that dropped as a low as a sixteenth of a mile at Baton Rouge, La.
   A dense fog advisory was in effect until midmorning for
east-central Louisiana.
   Today's forecast: showers and thunderstorms from the eastern
half of the Gulf Coast region across northern and central Florida,
the Tennessee Valley and the middle Atlantic Coast; showers from
the Virginias across New England and the lower Great Lakes; winds
strong and gusty from the upper Mississippi Valley across the
northern Plains into the northern Rockies.
   High temperatures were to reach the 40s and 50s from the
northern Atlantic Coast across the northern Ohio Valley to the
Great Lakes states; the 60s and 70s along the Virginia and the
southern Atlantic coasts, the southern Ohio Valley, the central
Gulf Coast states, the Mississippi Valley, much of the Plains, the
northern and central Rockies, and much of the Pacific Coast; the
80s in southwest Texas, the southern Rockies, much of the southern
Plateau and the inland California; and the 90s across the desert
Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 24
degrees at Custer, S.D., to 78 at Phoenix and Miami.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 55 showers; Boston 38 fair; Buffalo 50 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 62 cloudy; Cincinnati 48 cloudy; Cleveland 53
cloudy; Detroit 45 partly cloudy; Miami 78 partly cloudy; New York
45 cloudy; Philadelphia 47 cloudy; Pittsburgh 53 cloudy; Portland,
Maine 31 foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck 29 fair; Chicago 47 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
47 fair; Denver 48 fair; Des Moines 43 fair; Indianapolis 50 rain;
Kansas City 44 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 36 fair; Nashville 50
foggy; New Orleans 63 foggy; St. Louis 50 rain.
   _West: Albuquerque 54 fair; Anchorage 40 cloudy; Las Vegas 71
fair; Los Angeles 60 cloudy; Phoenix 78 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 56 cloudy; San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco 55 partly
cloudy; Seattle 53 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 43 cloudy; Toronto 41 rain.
