<DOCNO> AP890415-0038 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-04-15-89 1045EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Ireland-Theater     04-15 0082</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Ireland-Theater,0083</SECOND>
<HEAD>Abbey Theater Director Resigns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vincent Dowling has resigned as artistic
director of the Abbey Theater and will become director-producer for
development in the United States and Canada, the theater announced
Saturday.
   Dowling, now appearing in a student production of ``King Lear''
in Chicago, is the fourth artistic director to resign in as many
years. Noel Pearson, executive chairman of the national theater,
will serve as artistic director until a successor is appointed, the
company said.
</TEXT>
