<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--PriceyLand     04-15 0135</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Pricey Land,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tokyo Land Prices 30-100 Times Higher Than In Cities Overseas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Land prices in Tokyo are 30 to nearly 100 times
higher than in other major cities, according to results of a survey
reported Saturday.
   The survey found land in Tokyo costs nearly 100 times more than
in Los Angeles, 50 times more than in Sydney, Australia and 30
times more than in London, Kyodo News Service reported.
   Kyodo said the survey by the Japanese Association of Real Estate
Appraisal compared land prices in residential and commercial areas
in 14 cities.
   The average price of 1.2 square yards of land in Setagaya, an
affluent residential area in Tokyo, exceeds $7,600, Kyodo said.
   In comparison, it said, the same parcel costs about $83 in Los
Angeles and $273 in London.
</TEXT>
