<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Drugs,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nine More Drug Smugglers Hanged in Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine drug smugglers were hanged Saturday
in three cities, Tehran radio reported.
   The hangings brought the number of executions to 388 since
January 21, when a law took effect mandating the death sentence for
anyone caught possessing even small quantities of narcotics.
   The radio report, monitored in Nicosia, said police seized more
than 2,000 pounds of opium, 50 pounds of opium essence and 22
pounds of heroin from the nine.
   It also said 10 more drug smugglers had been arrested and more
than 180 pounds of narcotics and small arms were seized.
   Iranian have arrested hundreds of people allegedly involved in
drug trafficking and use. Most of the arrests have been made near
Iran's borders with Afghanistan and Pakistan.
