Useful Theater Company.
   During a visit to Britain earlier this month, Mikhail S.
Gorbachev invited the queen to visit Moscow, and she accepted.
   She would be the first British monarch to visit the Soviet Union
since the 1917 revolution that overthrew the czar. Czar Nicholas
II, a cousin of the queen's grandfather, was murdered with his
family in 1918 by the Bolsheviks.
