World Cup Equestrian Festival this weekend. The spotlight also is
on Princess Anne, who is attending amid speculation her marriage of
15 years is in trouble.
   The 38-year-old princess arrived at the Tampa International
Airport on Friday night and was whisked away without speaking to
reporters.
   Princess Anne, president of Federation Equestre Internationale,
is to stay for three days, her eighth visit to the United States.
She is scheduled to present awards at World Cup closing cermonies
Sunday.
   Letters to Princess Anne from an aide to Queen Elizabeth II have
prompted speculation that her marriage to Capt. Mark Phillips, a
fellow equestrian, is on the rocks. Phillips did not make the trip.
