<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Deb of the Decade is getting down
and dirty with the grease monkeys.
   Cornelia Guest planned to be down in the pits with a group of
celebs and former pro drivers for today's Toyota Pro-Celebrity race
through the streets of downtown Long Beach.
   Other celebrities in the race are comedian Jay Leno, former pro
football running back Walter Payton, and actors Danny Glover,
Kelsey Grammer, Ricky Schroder and Brian Wimmer.
   The oh-so-proper Guest _ the daughter of C.Z. Guest and the
goddaughter of Sir Winston Churchill _ will drive one of the Toyota
Celica GT-S Liftback race cars.
   ``It's a sport of precision and concentration, and it's a great
challenge,'' she said. ``One of the things I really like about it
is that once you get in your car, no matter what you're bringing
with you, debutante or whatever, it's just you in that car.''
   Guest's first movie, ``Second Sight,'' is due out this summer.
She has written ``The Debutante's Guide to Life,'' a
tongue-in-cheek look at high society.
